don't use these tools, how do you do it? Do you just remember every type and field in a codebase? What does your flow look like?<p>One example is that I cannot live without the language server go-to-definition feature. What do you do if you need to look up the definition/implementation of some function which is in some other file?</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42492508\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42492508</a></p>\n<p>Points: 251</p>\n<p># Comments: 495</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"Hoarder: Self-hostable bookmark-everything app","url":"https://github.com/hoarder-app/hoarder","date":1734867257,"author":"thunderbong","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"\n<p>Article URL: <a href=\"https://github.com/hoarder-app/hoarder\">https://github.com/hoarder-app/hoarder</a></p>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42485746\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42485746</a></p>\n<p>Points: 239</p>\n<p># Comments: 52</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""},{"title":"More men are addicted to the 'crack cocaine' of the stock market","url":"https://www.wsj.com/finance/stocks/stock-market-trading-apps-addiction-afecb07a","date":1734668510,"author":"marban","unread":true,"desc":"","content":"\n<p>Article URL: <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/finance/stocks/stock-market-trading-apps-addiction-afecb07a\">https://www.wsj.com/finance/stocks/stock-market-trading-apps-addiction-afecb07a</a></p>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42468255\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=42468255</a></p>\n<p>Points: 184</p>\n<p># Comments: 398</p>\n","flags":null,"enclosureUrl":"","enclosureMime":""}]}